race.comment: AIN'T NO OTHER MAN (1) is coming back from Saturday grade where he was 2.9L off the winner. His recent form is rather plain, but he wasn't beaten far in a similar race back in August. Needs some luck from out wide, but the claim comes in handy and he can bounce back to his best. UNIVERSAL PLAYBOY (4) is a different horse when he can find the front, and that was on display last start at Pinjarra when bolting in over this trip. Rises in weight, but maps to find the front again for Altieri with the Barton stable really starting to heat up. Plenty to like about him. HISTORY WON'T CARE (10) looks a nice type, though he lands here without a trial first-up. Winkers replace the blinkers, with the booking of Pike suggesting he's going well enough at home. Can fire fresh. LET'S TALK (8) can improve again now third-up and back in grade. ON PATROL (6) was solid fresh and ticks a few boxes today.
